Phase 7 #14 (in-call-state) shipped on 2026-05-18:
- Tier 2 single-session (~55K Opus controller, fully inline execution per user choice after #13's Sonnet thrash). User picked (in-call-state) from the recommended-next slot.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/in-call.ts` (149 lines) — `createInCallRoster()` returns `Map<orgId, Map<userId, Set<socketId>>>` with `{wasFirst}/{isLast}` coalescing parallel to Phase 7 #11's presence roster; `attachInCallHandlers({io, socket, roster})` joins `${orgId}:call:active` via `joinOrgChannel`, sends `call:active-snapshot` socket-direct on connect, listens for `call:joined`/`call:left` browser emits, broadcasts `call:active {userId, in_call}` org-scoped via `emitToOrg` only on 0↔1 transitions, registers a disconnect cleanup handler.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/in-call.test.ts` (242 lines, 11 RED→GREEN) — 5 roster contract cases + 6 handler-wiring cases (joinOrgChannel call, socket-direct snapshot, broadcast on wasFirst, no-broadcast on second socket, disconnect cleanup isLast, defensive no-session no-op). Hand-rolled MinimalSocket + IOServer fakes per [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/presence/in-call-handler.ts` (77 lines) — pure handler `attachInCallHandlers(socket, {onRoster, onUpdate})` mirroring `user-presence-handler.ts` byte-for-byte; overloaded `MinimalInCallSocketTarget` interface so real TypedSocket gets strict payload types; node-testable per [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/presence/in-call-handler.test.ts` (117 lines, 5 RED→GREEN) — register both listeners, snapshot callback, update callback, disposer unwires, no-callbacks-after-dispose. Hand-rolled fake matching user-presence-handler.test.ts structure.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/presence/use-users-in-call.ts` (69 lines) — `useUsersInCall(userIds): ReadonlySet<string>` React hook consuming `useSocketOptional()` from Phase 7 #10's SocketProvider + `attachInCallHandlers`; returns full org in-call set (callers do `.has()` check via helper). Jsdom test deferred per Phase 7 #11 precedent.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/livekit/use-emit-call-participation.ts` (52 lines) — composable hook `useEmitCallParticipation(room: Room | null)` wiring `socket.emit("call:joined"|"call:left")` to `RoomEvent.Connected`/`Disconnected`. No-op when socket or room is null. Invoked from BOTH `useLiveKitRoom` (intercom 1:1) AND `useMeetingRoom` (multi-participant meetings) so both flows feed the same roster.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/types.ts` (+12 lines) — 2 new `ServerToClientEvents` (`call:active` + `call:active-snapshot`) + 2 new `ClientToServerEvents` (`call:joined` + `call:left`). Distinct from `presence:user`/`presence:snapshot` to keep type-map collisions impossible.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/socket/server.ts` (+11 lines) — instantiate `createInCallRoster()` once at server boot; wire `attachInCallHandlers` inside existing `io.on("connection")` callback alongside `attachPresenceHandlers`.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/department-presence.ts` (+17 lines) — `selectDepartmentPresence(dept, online, inCall: ReadonlySet<string>)` adds 3rd parameter with locked precedence JSDoc: unbound → offline; `inCall.has` → in_call (wins); online → online; else → offline.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/department-presence.test.ts` (+51 lines) — existing 5 selectDepartmentPresence cases updated to pass empty Set; +4 new cases: in_call basic, precedence wins over online, precedence wins over offline (transitional window edge case), null FK still wins as offline even if id is in inCall set.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/speed-dial-grid.tsx` (+4 lines) — `useUsersInCall(boundUserIds)` import + hook call + 3rd arg to `selectDepartmentPresence`.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/livekit/use-livekit-room.ts` (+6 lines) + `apps/web/src/lib/livekit/use-meeting-room.ts` (+5 lines) — both invoke `useEmitCallParticipation(roomInstance)` right before their return statement.
- Test suite 124 → 144 (+20 RED→GREEN, exactly as planned: 5 roster + 6 server-handler + 5 client-handler + 4 helper). pnpm typecheck ✓ 0 errors 8 packages (caught latent SocketSession.role missing on TEST_SESSION during Task 3 — fixed via `role: "host"` add). pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors. pnpm build ✓ 22 static + dynamic routes + middleware 140kB (MANDATORY per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — in-call.ts is in createSocketServer import chain). pnpm audit --audit-level=critical ✓ exit 0 (Phase 7 #9 + #10 still in effect; 1 HIGH = documented nodemailer per [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]). Two-stage review (Rule 25): Stage 1 spec PASS (8/8 locked items: client-emit trigger source, twin-roster/twin-hook separation, in_call > online > offline precedence, {wasFirst}/{isLast} multi-tab semantics, org-scoped channel via joinOrgChannel, socket-direct snapshot, calls.ts diff EMPTY, event names consistent across types.ts + in-call.ts + in-call-handler.ts + use-emit-call-participation.ts); Stage 2 quality PASS (8/8 — zero any types, TDD RED→GREEN verified, all 20 cases cover all branches, only 13 blast-radius files modified, conventional commits, no event-name drift, idiomatic React with useEffect cleanup + lazy useState for empty Set, Edge-build green).
- 0 new lessons logged — existing patterns covered everything ([[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]], [[presence-roster-coalesce-pattern]], [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]], [[event-handler-disposer-test-pattern]], [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]], [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]).
- 8 branch commits: `201eb67` server roster+handler, `4d72051` socket types, `d89d35d` wire createSocketServer, `7b28f0b` client handler, `106360a` useUsersInCall hook, `47ee55a` helper sig + SpeedDialGrid wiring, `44b9353` useEmitCallParticipation hook, `c0b3d6c` LiveKit hooks wiring. Plan execution: Tasks 1+2 collapsed into one TDD commit (roster+handler form the natural unit when all cases are written up front); Task 7 absorbed Task 9's SpeedDialGrid wiring (useUsersInCall already existed from Task 6 — skipped placeholder empty-Set commit). Subagent dispatch not used this ticket — fully inline per user choice after #13's thrash.
- Squash SHA: `6d3b6f8`. Closes (in-call-state). Closes the second deferred-scope item from Phase 7 #12. End-to-end flow now live: caller initiates → both browsers join LiveKit Room → both emit `call:joined` → server broadcasts `call:active` for both userIds → every Speed Dial Board in the org sees the YELLOW dot + disabled state on bound departments. Refinement vs spec: integration point uses a composable `useEmitCallParticipation` hook invoked from both LiveKit room hooks (instead of inline edits in the call page) — cleaner separation, works for both intercom AND meeting flows.

