Phase 7 #12 (department-binding) shipped on 2026-05-17:
- Tier 2 single-session (~55K Opus context). User picked (department-binding) from the recommended-next slot.
- NEW `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/department-presence.ts` (30 lines) — two pure helpers `extractBoundUserIds(departments): string[]` (filters nulls, preserves order) + `selectDepartmentPresence(department, online): PresenceState` (returns "online" only when default_user_id is non-null AND online[default_user_id] === true; else "offline"). Node-testable per [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] — no React import.
- NEW `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/department-presence.test.ts` (75 lines, 9 RED→GREEN cases) — full helper contract proven: 4 for extractBoundUserIds (empty input, null-filtering, order preservation, no-dedup) + 5 for selectDepartmentPresence (bound+online, bound+offline, bound+missing-from-map, unbound (null FK) returns offline, defensive undefined entry).
- NEW Prisma migration `20260517075117_add_department_default_user_id` — `ALTER TABLE "departments" ADD COLUMN "default_user_id" TEXT` + index + FK to `users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL ON UPDATE CASCADE`. TEXT type matches cuid() id convention across all 13 models (NOT UUID — plan's `@db.Uuid` was caught wrong at pre-flight read of schema.prisma).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/speed-dial/speed-dial-grid.tsx` (+9 / -4 lines) — local Department interface widened with `default_user_id: string | null`; `usePresence(ids)` replaced with `useUserPresence(extractBoundUserIds(departments))`; `presenceState` prop derived via `selectDepartmentPresence(dept, online)`. `<SpeedDialButton>` untouched.
- MODIFIED `packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma` (+5 on Department, +1 inverse on User) — `default_user_id String?` + `default_user User? @relation("DepartmentDefaultUser", ...)` + `@@index([default_user_id])`. Inverse `default_for_departments Department[]` on User. Named relation disambiguates from future Department→User relations.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/app/app/page.tsx` (+1 line) — `default_user_id: true` in Prisma select clause so the SC's typed prop flows the new field through.
- DELETED `apps/web/src/lib/presence/use-presence.ts` (-55 lines) — legacy department-level stub. Sole consumer migrated; closes the cleanup started in Phase 7 #11. Legacy `presence:update` event in types.ts is now orphaned but stays until (legacy-socket-retirement) lands.
- 9 new RED→GREEN cases (test suite 108→117). pnpm build ✓ 27 routes in 1m26s (per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — schema change → prisma generate → bundle impact verified). pnpm audit ✓ exit 0 (Phase 7 #9 acceptance + #10 CLI flag still in effect). Two-stage review (Rule 25) PASS — all 5 locked spec decisions verified, no `any`, no type assertions, scope strictly bounded to plan inventory.
- 0 new lessons logged — nothing novel emerged (existing patterns covered everything; cuid/UUID discovery was a pre-flight catch not a runtime gotcha; pre-flight pattern is already encoded in Rule 4).
- Squash SHA: (set in next governance commit). Closes (department-binding). The Speed Dial Board now shows real per-department green dots when the bound user is connected — first end-to-end realtime UX surface using the Phase 7 #11 engine. `selectDepartmentPresence(department, online)` is the framework precedent for any future "derive single-resource state from user-presence map" pattern.

Phase 7 #11 (presence) shipped on 2026-05-17:
- Tier 2 single-session (~70K Opus context). User picked (presence) from the recommended-next slot.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/presence.ts` — `createPresenceRoster()` returns a pure in-memory `Map<orgId, Map<userId, Set<socketId>>>` with `addSocket → {wasFirst}` / `removeSocket → {isLast}` semantics. Multi-tab coalescing means we broadcast ONLY on real online/offline transitions (the 0↔1 socket-count threshold for a user), not on every per-tab connect/disconnect.
- NEW `attachPresenceHandlers({io, socket, roster})` — joins `${orgId}:presence:user` via `joinOrgChannel`, emits `presence:user {userId, online:true}` to the org channel iff wasFirst, sends `presence:snapshot {userIds[]}` socket-direct (including self), registers a disconnect handler that emits `presence:user {online:false}` iff isLast. Defensive no-session bail.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/presence/user-presence-handler.ts` — pure handler `attachUserPresenceHandlers(socket, {onRoster, onUpdate})` returning disposer. Overloaded `MinimalSocketEventTarget` interface so real TypedSocket consumers get exact payload typing. Node-testable (no React import).
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/presence/use-user-presence.ts` — "use client" React hook `useUserPresence(userIds): Record<userId, boolean>`. Consumes `useSocketOptional()` from Phase 7 #10's SocketProvider — no new socket per consumer. Graceful degradation when socket null.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/socket/server.ts` — `createPresenceRoster()` instantiated once, wired via `io.on("connection", socket => attachPresenceHandlers(...))` AFTER the auth middleware so `socket.data.session` is guaranteed.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/types.ts` — added `presence:user` + `presence:snapshot` to ServerToClientEvents (distinct names from legacy `presence:update` to avoid type-map collision with the still-live /api/socket path).
- MIGRATED `apps/web/src/lib/presence/use-presence.ts` — gutted the broken `io(NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL)` connection + `presence:subscribe`/`presence:heartbeat` emits + 30s heartbeat interval. Now consumes `useSocketOptional()` and returns a frozen all-offline `Record<departmentId, "offline">`. Public `<SpeedDialGrid>` contract preserved exactly so no consumers had to change. Department-Binding follow-up ticket wires real per-department state.
- 23 new RED→GREEN cases (test suite 85→108). pnpm build ✓ 27 routes (per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — new module is in createSocketServer chain). pnpm audit ✓ exit 0 (Phase 7 #9 acceptance + #10 CLI flag still in effect). Two-stage review (Rule 25) PASS.
- 2 new lessons: 🟤 [[presence-roster-coalesce-pattern]], 🟤 [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]].
- Squash SHA: `81356e9`. Closes (presence). Unblocks every realtime org-scoped feature — `emitToOrg(io, organizationId, eventType, payload)` with `joinOrgChannel` enforcing zero cross-org leakage is now the framework precedent.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Candidates for Phase 7 #14 (any order, user picks):
----------------------------------------------------------------------

(i) Periodic cleanup of expired/consumed password_reset_tokens
    BullMQ scheduled job to DELETE consumed tokens > 30 days old and unconsumed expired tokens > 7 days. Keeps the table from
    growing unboundedly. Pairs naturally with #6: the cap-met silent-skip and the cleanup job together close the token-table
    lifecycle. The count query introduced in #6 stays fast forever if the cleanup runs daily.
    Tier 2 (BullMQ worker + scheduler + tests + deploy config).

(d) join/[token] tRPC                          [needs LiveKit ⏳ for full integration]
    Unit tests OK against mocked LiveKit token mint; integration deferred until LIVEKIT_API_KEY filled.
    Existing getJoinToken in meetingsRouter has 0 test coverage — could pair with this if scope allows.

(f) Root landing page                          [verify scope first]
    Current /page.tsx is 11 lines — check PRODUCT.md for what's expected. Likely Tier 1.

(legacy-socket-retirement) Retire legacy /api/socket Socket.IO server — Tier 2, RECOMMENDED NEXT
    Now that the auth-gated server on SOCKET_PORT carries presence (Phase 7 #11), session-invalidation
    (Phase 7 #8e-2), and in-call broadcast (Phase 7 #14), the new server is the obvious primary.
    The legacy `apps/web/src/lib/socket/server.ts` + `apps/web/src/app/api/socket/route.ts` exist
    only for the calls router's `emitIncomingCall` flow. Migrate `emitIncomingCall` to use
    `emitToOrg(io, organizationId, "call:incoming", payload)` via the new server, then delete
    the legacy module + route + the `subscribedDepartmentIds`/`callIncomingRoom`/`callerRoom`/
    `presence:update` types in lib/socket/types.ts. Closes [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]]
    decision by collapsing to one server. Single source of truth for socket events.

(rule-16-cleanup) Visual QA debt batch          [pairs naturally with department-binding — recommended companion]
    Now that build is green again on `main`, clear accumulated smoke tests:
    - /forgot-password + /reset-password (Phase 7 #4 carryover)
    - /app/meetings/new (#3 carryover)
    - subdomain redirect (#7c carryover) — `acme.localhost` / `evil.localhost` in /etc/hosts OR /t/{slug} path pattern
    - Socket.IO handshake (Phase 7 #8e carryover) — `curl http://localhost:43515/socket.io/` returns handshake page + browser
      session in /app connects to ws://localhost:43515
    - Socket.IO session:invalidated trigger (Phase 7 #10) — open a tab in /app, trigger session invalidation in another tab
      (sign out OR admin disables user), wait ≤60s, verify connected socket receives `session:invalidated` event AND the tab
      redirects to /login automatically.
    - NEW: Presence engine smoke (Phase 7 #11) — open two browser tabs (same user), verify the snapshot includes self AND
      another peer in the same org. Sign out / close one tab — verify other tab does NOT see user go offline (multi-tab
      coalescing held). Close the last tab — verify peers in the org receive `presence:user {online:false}` within transport
      timeout (~25s pingInterval + 20s pingTimeout = ~45s worst-case).
    - NEW: Speed Dial green-dot smoke (Phase 7 #12) — open pgAdmin, bind one demo department's `default_user_id` to the
      webmaster user id (UPDATE departments SET default_user_id = '<webmaster-id>' WHERE name = 'Reception'). Sign in as
      webmaster in /app → wait for socket handshake (~1s) → verify the Reception speed-dial button shows a green dot AND is
      clickable (not disabled). Sign out → wait for transport timeout (~45s) → verify the dot returns to gray AND the button
      becomes disabled. Verify an unbound department (default_user_id IS NULL) stays gray + disabled throughout (matches
      existing offline UX).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Rule 25 reminder for ALL of the above:
  → Write failing test FIRST (RED), then implementation (GREEN), then refactor.
  → Test patterns:
      [[trpc-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #2)
      [[meetings-protected-route-test]] (Phase 7 #3)
      [[trpc-test-with-env-mock]] (Phase 7 #4)
      [[direct-callback-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-1 — exercises authConfig.callbacks directly)
      [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-2 / #8e / #10 / #11 — extract Edge-incompatible or React-incompatible code into separate file for Node test runner)
      [[socket-auth-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #8e-1 — mock next-auth/jwt decode + assert decode receives correct salt)
      [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #8e-2 — mock io.fetchSockets + prisma.user.findMany; assert disconnect/emit per stale-session branch)
      [[socket-client-factory-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #10 — vi.mock("socket.io-client"); assert io() receives correct URL + opts)
      [[event-handler-disposer-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #10 — hand-rolled MinimalSocket fake; assert register/fire/dispose/no-cross-fire)
      [[presence-roster-coalesce-pattern]] (Phase 7 #11 — Map<orgId, Map<userId, Set<socketId>>> with {wasFirst}/{isLast} semantics; mock io.to(...).emit(...) per [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]] precedent)
      [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-2 / #8e / #10 / #11 / #12 — extract React-incompatible OR Edge-incompatible OR simply node-testable logic into a separate file; the React component becomes a thin composition that's correct-by-construction)
  → For forms: reuse the [[shadcn-form-primitive]] pattern from Phase 7 #3.
  → For shared schemas: `<Entity>CreateClientInputSchema` for client-facing input, `<Entity>CreateInputSchema` for admin/internal projection.
  → For new env vars consumed by routers: add `vi.mock("@/env", ...)` to the test file.
  → For new JWT fields: wire BOTH session callbacks (auth.config.ts Edge-safe AND auth.ts DB-revalidating) — see [[edge-safe-vs-db-revalidating-callback-duplication]].
  → For new Auth.js v5 decode contexts (anywhere outside Next.js itself): pass the COOKIE NAME as the `salt` parameter — see [[authjs-v5-jwe-cookie-salt]].
  → For new Socket.IO room subscriptions: use the org-scoped helper pattern (`joinOrgChannel(socket, eventType)` with no org-id parameter) — see [[socket-cross-org-api-surface-guard]].
  → For new Socket.IO client events emitted from React: consume via `useSocket()` from `@/lib/socket/socket-context` — do NOT instantiate `io()` directly.
  → For new realtime broadcast features (org-scoped fan-out): follow the `emitToOrg(io, organizationId, eventType, payload)` pattern; never accept an orgId parameter on the subscription path (sourced from session only).
  → For multi-tab presence/notification engines: use the `{wasFirst}`/`{isLast}` roster coalescing pattern from Phase 7 #11 to avoid flicker on tab refresh / HMR / reconnect.
  → For new events added to lib/socket/types.ts: use DISTINCT event names from any legacy event (the legacy /api/socket server still consumes the same type map — see [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]]).
  → When a router becomes fully tested (>95% across all four metrics), add a per-file threshold to apps/web/vitest.config.ts — see [[vitest-per-file-glob-thresholds]].
  → Coverage thresholds rise organically — add tests → measure → bump threshold. Do NOT lower thresholds to make a regression "fix" pass.
  → NEW (Phase 7 #6): for any new throttle/cap design on auth flows, follow [[per-user-24h-cap-pattern]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #7c): for any work that touches CLAUDE.md / .claude/rules/* / governance docs, prefer Opus-executor over Sonnet dispatch — Sonnet subagents thrash on SessionStart hooks. See [[sonnet-thrash-sessionstart-hooks]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #7c): for any middleware.ts edit, IGNORE the vercel-plugin nextjs auto-suggestion to rename to proxy.ts — Yelli is on Next.js 15.5.18. See [[proxy-ts-false-positive]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #9): for unfixed HIGH CVEs in transitively-pinned deps, follow the 5-step decision tree in [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]] — trace exploit reachability, JSDoc the call site, DECISIONS_LOG entry with revisit triggers, `.npmrc audit-level=critical`, AND a matching `--audit-level=critical` CLI flag in CI (per #10 correction).
  → NEW (Phase 7 #10): for any work touching `apps/web/src/instrumentation.ts` or its transitively-imported modules, MUST run `pnpm build` as part of validation per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]]. test/typecheck/lint are not sufficient to catch Edge-bundle webpack failures.
  → NEW (Phase 7 #10): for any audit policy claim, run `pnpm audit` BARE (no flag) and verify exit code — `.npmrc audit-level` does NOT control the bare exit code on pnpm 10. See [[pnpm10-audit-level-ignored]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #11): test fakes that need to satisfy overloaded interfaces (per-event-name payload typing) use a `loose as unknown as Interface` boundary cast — established precedent `} as never` (revalidation.test.ts) and `as unknown as IOServer` (channels.test.ts). Keeps production typing strict while letting test runtime be loose.

Recommended next: (legacy-socket-retirement) — with #14 shipping 4 more events (`call:active`, `call:active-snapshot`, `call:joined`, `call:left`) on the auth-gated server, the new server is now the obvious primary. The legacy /api/socket only carries `emitIncomingCall`; migrate it to `emitToOrg` and delete the legacy module + route + orphaned `subscribedDepartmentIds`/`callIncomingRoom`/`callerRoom`/`presence:update` types. Closes [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]]. OR (rule-16-cleanup) for accumulated smoke-test debt now that we have THREE realtime engines wired into UI (presence green dot since #12, admin self-service since #13, in-call yellow dot since #14). OR (i) BullMQ cleanup as clean Tier 2 housekeeping. Save (d) join/[token] for when LIVEKIT_API_KEY is filled. (f) root landing is a tiny fill-in if you want to clear the smallest open ticket first.

Pending Rule 16 follow-up (accumulated debt — clear before Phase 7 #N+M):
  - smoke-test /app/meetings/new in browser after next `pnpm dev` up (Phase 7 #3 carryover)
  - smoke-test /forgot-password + /reset-password/[token] — public routes, no credentials needed (Phase 7 #4 carryover). With the 24h cap live, manual /forgot-password smoke for the same email is limited to 5 requests per 24h — use distinct emails or trust test assertions
  - smoke-test subdomain routing (Phase 7 #7c carryover) — edit /etc/hosts with `acme.localhost` / `evil.localhost`, OR use the /t/{slug} path pattern. Log in as user with org "acme" → visit http://localhost:43512/t/evil/app → confirm redirects to /t/acme/app. Super-admin → visit /t/evil/superadmin/users → confirm allows (option C bypass); visit /t/evil/app → confirm redirects to own subdomain
  - smoke-test Socket.IO handshake + session:invalidated event (Phase 7 #8e + #10 carryover). (1) start dev env with SOCKET_PORT=43515; (2) `curl http://localhost:43515/socket.io/` returns Socket.IO handshake page; (3) browser session in /app connects to ws://localhost:43515 + console logs no errors; (4) trigger session invalidation in another tab (sign out, or admin disables user) → wait ≤60s → verify the connected socket receives `session:invalidated` event AND the tab redirects to /login automatically.
  - NEW smoke-test Presence engine (Phase 7 #11). Open two browser tabs as the SAME user → both connect → both receive `presence:snapshot` containing self (plus any other peer in the org). Close ONE of the two tabs → OTHER tab should NOT see user go offline (multi-tab coalescing). Close the LAST tab → peers in the org should receive `presence:user {online:false}` within transport timeout (~25s pingInterval + 20s pingTimeout = ~45s worst case). Confirm the cross-org isolation: a user in `org-acme` should NEVER see a `presence:user` event for a user in `org-evil`.
  - NEW smoke-test Speed Dial green-dot UI (Phase 7 #12). pgAdmin: UPDATE departments SET default_user_id = '<webmaster-id>' WHERE name = '<demo-dept-name>'. Sign in as webmaster in /app → wait ~1s for socket handshake → verify the bound department's speed-dial button shows a green dot AND is clickable (not disabled). Sign out → wait ~45s for transport timeout → verify the dot returns to gray AND the button becomes disabled. Verify an unbound department (default_user_id IS NULL) stays gray + disabled throughout. Verify a department bound to a user in a DIFFERENT org never shows online (cross-org isolation via the org-scoped Socket.IO channel). Verify the auto_answer badge ⚡ Auto still renders correctly for departments that have it set (orthogonal to presence).
  - NEW smoke-test admin-binding-ui (Phase 7 #13). Open /admin/departments as tenant_admin → pick a user from a department's "Default user" dropdown → verify mutation fires (toast appears) → refresh Speed Dial Board in /app → verify the bound dept's dot color flips to green (if user is online). Clear binding → verify the dot returns to gray. Visit /admin/departments as a non-admin role → verify redirect to /app. Bind to a deactivated user via direct SQL → verify the dropdown shows "(deactivated)" cosmetically and offers a clear option.
  - NEW smoke-test in-call yellow-dot UI (Phase 7 #14). Two browser tabs as DIFFERENT users in the SAME org (e.g. webmaster bound to "Reception", and a second user bound to "Sales"). Tab A initiates a call to tab B's bound dept → both tabs auto-navigate into /app/call/[id] → both LiveKit Room.Connected events fire → both browsers emit call:joined → server broadcasts call:active for both userIds → every Speed Dial Board open in the org now shows YELLOW dot + disabled state on Reception AND Sales. Hang up (either side) → Room.Disconnected fires → both emit call:left → server broadcasts call:active in_call:false → dots return to GREEN (still socket-online). Sign out of one tab → wait ~45s for transport timeout → that user's bound dept dot returns to GRAY. Cross-org isolation: open a third tab as a user in a DIFFERENT org → should NEVER see the yellow dot for any user in org-A.
